# Website — Edit & Deploy

## Source of Truth

All website files live in **`imin-backend/web/marketing/`**. This is the canonical source.

**WARNING: `imin-site` repo is NOT the source of truth for VPS deployment!**
VPS receives files ONLY from `imin-backend/web/marketing/` (via SCP and blog-sync).
**NEVER edit website in `imin-site` expecting it to appear on VPS.**

```
web/marketing/
├── index.template.html     # Skeleton with <!--@include ...--> directives
├── sections/               # ← EDIT THESE (source of truth for content)
│   ├── _head.html          # <head>: metadata, JSON-LD
│   ├── 01-hero.html
│   ├── 02-about.html
│   ├── 03-features.html    # 12 feature cards
│   ├── 04-whatsnew.html    # Latest release highlights
│   ├── 05-showcase-map.html
│   ├── 06-showcase-community.html
│   ├── 07-showcase-content.html
│   ├── 08-how-it-works.html
│   ├── 09-download.html
│   ├── 10-faq.html
│   ├── 11-contact.html
│   ├── _footer.html
│   └── _scripts.html
├── build.py                # Concatenates partials → index.html
├── index.html              # ⚙️ GENERATED — never hand-edit; commit alongside partials
├── blog.html               # Blog: hardcoded "Product News" + dynamic "Travel News"
├── styles.css              # All CSS
├── translations.js         # Lean translation engine (lazy-loads language JSON)
├── translations/           # Per-language JSON files — edit these
│   ├── uk.json             # Ukrainian (canonical — keep in sync with HTML defaults)
│   ├── en.json, fr.json, es.json, de.json, it.json, el.json
├── script.js               # Animations, parallax, interactions
├── privacy.html/terms.html # Legal pages
├── 404.html, robots.txt, sitemap.xml, manifest.json, favicon.svg
└── *.png                   # Images (logo, app screenshots)
```

### Build workflow

Edit ONLY partials in `sections/`. Then rebuild `index.html`:

```bash
cd /Users/igorkravchenko/Documents/imin-backend/web/marketing
python3 build.py             # rebuilds index.html
python3 build.py --check     # CI: verify index.html matches sections/
```

Directive syntax: `<!--@include sections/xxx.html-->` — place at **column 0**; the partial itself carries its own indentation. Paths are relative to the file that contains the directive. Pure stdlib, no deps.

**Commit both `sections/*.html` AND the generated `index.html`** — blog-sync fetches the built `index.html` from GitLab raw, not the partials.

## How Translations Work

**Lean engine + per-language JSON (lazy-loaded):**

- `translations.js` (~6KB) — engine only: detects language, fetches `translations/<lang>.json` on demand, caches it, applies to `[data-translate]` / `[data-translate-placeholder]`
- `translations/uk.json`, `en.json`, `fr.json`, `es.json`, `de.json`, `it.json`, `el.json` — each ~21–33KB
- Users download **engine + 1 language file** (≈ 27–39KB) instead of the old 173KB single bundle
- Default HTML text is Ukrainian so UK users see correct copy instantly; other languages swap in once their JSON arrives
- Key lookup uses dotted paths (`features.aiRoute.title`). Missing keys return the key unchanged (visible raw in the page → easy to spot in QA)
- If translation contains HTML tags (`<a>`, `<b>`, `<span>`, etc.) → `innerHTML`; otherwise → `textContent`
- **7 languages**: uk, en, fr, es, de, it, el — update ALL `translations/*.json` together when changing any text
- When you touch any JSON or translations.js, bump `CACHE_BUST` constant at the top of `translations.js` AND `?v=` query params in `sections/_head.html` (CSS) and `sections/_scripts.html` (JS) to force browsers off old cached copies
- Deploy BOTH `translations.js` AND the `translations/` directory (7 JSON files)

## Deployment — Manual SCP

```bash
# 1. Edit files in imin-backend/web/marketing/
# 2. Commit & push to GitLab
cd /Users/igorkravchenko/Documents/imin-backend
git add web/marketing/
git commit -m "website: description of change"
git push

# 3. SCP changed files to VPS
scp web/marketing/index.html web/marketing/translations.js \
    deploy@135.125.254.131:/var/www/im-in.net/html/
```

| What | VPS Path |
|---|---|
| Root files (index.html, styles.css, etc.) | `/var/www/im-in.net/html/` |
| Blog posts (auto-generated) | `/var/www/im-in.net/html/blog/` |

SSH: `deploy@135.125.254.131` (key-only, `~/.ssh/id_ed25519`)

## Auto-Sync (social-automation)

`blog_sync.py` in `social-automation` runs daily at 21:00 Kyiv:

1. Generates blog post HTML pages from DB → `blog/post-*.html`
2. Fetches website templates from **GitLab** (`imin-backend` raw files)
3. Injects blog links into `blog.html` between `<!-- BLOG_STATIC_LINKS_START -->` / `<!-- BLOG_STATIC_LINKS_END -->`
4. Pushes everything to VPS via API or SFTP

**Important**: blog-sync **overwrites** VPS files with GitLab versions. So always commit+push to GitLab before or after SCP — otherwise next blog-sync reverts your changes.

## Product News (blog.html)

Product news are **hardcoded HTML** inside `blog.html`, NOT from DB. Structure per language:

```html
<div class="product-news" data-lang="uk">
    <div class="news-card" style="border-left:4px solid #7C3AED">
        <div class="news-date">
            <div class="news-date-day">5</div>
            <div class="news-date-month">Кві 2026</div>
        </div>
        <div class="news-body">
            <h3>Title</h3>
            <p>Description</p>
            <span class="news-tag">Tag</span>
        </div>
    </div>
</div>
```

When adding product news: duplicate the card in ALL 7 language blocks (`data-lang="uk"`, `"en"`, `"fr"`, `"es"`, `"de"`, `"it"`, `"el"`).

## Travel News (blog.html)

Travel news come from `social-automation` DB via `blog_sync.py`. Auto-generated `post-*.html` files are placed in `/blog/` on VPS. Links injected between the markers above.

## Cloudflare CDN & Caching

Website is proxied through Cloudflare.

### Що кешується

| Контент | Кешування | Швидкість |
|---|---|---|
| `/downloads/imin-latest.apk` (257 MB) | **Кешується** (Edge 24h, Browser 1h) | ~10 MB/s з edge vs ~1.5 MB/s з VPS |
| `/downloads/android-version.json` | **Кешується** (Edge 24h, Browser 1h) | Миттєво |
| `index.html`, `styles.css`, `script.js` | Не кешується (DYNAMIC) | З VPS напряму |
| API responses | Не кешується | З VPS напряму |

### Після деплою website changes

HTML/CSS/JS мають `cf-cache-status: DYNAMIC` — зміни видно одразу, purge не потрібен.

### Після деплою APK (CI автоматично)

CI job `deploy:android-apk` автоматично робить cache purge для APK та version.json.

### Ручний purge (якщо потрібно)

```bash
ZONE_ID="3b4aa8fcc564391f111959297c243701"
# Purge конкретних файлів
curl -s -X POST "https://api.cloudflare.com/client/v4/zones/$ZONE_ID/purge_cache" \
  -H "X-Auth-Email: igork2011@gmail.com" \
  -H "X-Auth-Key: $CF_API_KEY" \
  -H "Content-Type: application/json" \
  --data '{"files":["https://www.im-in.net/downloads/imin-latest.apk","https://www.im-in.net/downloads/android-version.json"]}'

# Purge ВСЬОГО (обережно — скине весь кеш)
curl -s -X POST "https://api.cloudflare.com/client/v4/zones/$ZONE_ID/purge_cache" \
  -H "X-Auth-Email: igork2011@gmail.com" \
  -H "X-Auth-Key: $CF_API_KEY" \
  -H "Content-Type: application/json" \
  --data '{"purge_everything":true}'
```

Full Cloudflare docs: `imin-app/.cursor/rules/cloudflare-cdn.mdc`

## Checklist for Website Changes

1. Edit files in `imin-backend/web/marketing/`
2. If translations changed → update all 7 languages in `translations.js`
3. If HTML fallback text exists → update it too (for SEO / no-JS)
4. If JSON-LD schema has related info → update `<script type="application/ld+json">`
5. `git add && git commit && git push` to GitLab
6. `scp` changed files to `deploy@135.125.254.131:/var/www/im-in.net/html/`
7. Optionally purge Cloudflare cache (see above) for immediate effect
8. Verify in browser: `https://www.im-in.net/?v=N` (cache-bust with query param)
